attributeList.attribute: Group II Heat Shock Protein 60 chaperonins which catalyses the cytoplasmic ATP-dependent folding of newly synthesized proteins.

TCP1 displays a classic chaperonin architecture, with two heterogeneous 8-membered rings stacked back-to-back, enclosing a folding cavity. The two rings each contain eight different subunits that form a double-toroid. Each ring encloses a cavity volume of approximately 145 000 A E-3. The N- and C-termini of all subunits, except one, come together on the inside of the ring, in a network of beta-sheets at the ring-ring interface, which forms the 'cavity floor'.
Mol. wt = approximately 850 to 900 kDa
